  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of life saving drugs and disposables to respond to the emergency medical needs in Gaza.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a result of the Great Return March events, the burden on the already overstretched health system has increased to unbearable level. The MoH has been calling for immediate response from the health organizations working inside Gaza to assist with the provision of urgently needed drugs, disposables and surgical instruments. However, the Health Cluster indicated that an additional $19.2 million is urgently needed to cover the needs of the MoH and NGOs in managing trauma and providing essential healthcare until end September 2018. As of end of May, $6.3 million have been provided or pledged by various donors, leaving a gap of $12.9 million. While few organizations like MAP were able to respond immediately, the level of needs far more exceeds the provided response. Thus, MoH is still in dire need of drugs and disposables to be able to save the life of Palestinian patients in Gaza. MAP is planning to purchase a list of essential drugs and disposables to be delivered to Central Drug Stores in order to ensure the access of trauma and non-trauma patients to the treatment and medical care they need. The items procured will be contributing to the current emergency response projects that MAP is implementing in coordination with the health cluster, including the Limb Reconstruction (ortho/plastics), EMTs, Trauma, Zero-Stock, and the emergency support project.</narrative>
  </description>
